'''New Oldtown''' was a farming community on [[Aldivy]].

Sometime prior to [[7 ABY/Legends|7 ABY]], [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Apwar Trigit]] ordered the people of New Oldtown to provide his ship, the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Implacable (Star Destroyer)/Legends|''Implacable'']], with supplies. The people of the [[City/Legends|city]] refused, and Trigit obliterated the settlement. Very few citizens of New Oldtown survived, mostly natives who were out of the city at the time.

[[Lara Notsil]] and [[Tavin Notsil]] were natives of New Oldtown. Lara Notsil died in the bombardment, but Tavin Notsil was away at the time despite being sentenced to imprisonment in the city jail. When [[Gara Petothel]] assumed Lara's identity, [[Warlord/Legends|Warlord]] [[Zsinj]] had a temporary structure built on the ruins of New Oldtown where Petothel was to meet Tavin Notsil and a representative of Zsinj's forces.

Upon hearing the city's name, Warlord Zsinj immediately disliked it. He joked that perhaps Trigit had destroyed it because it has such a terrible name. He then ordered his second-in-command, [[General/Legends|General]] [[Melvar]], never to speak the city's name in his presence.

